    "narrative": "With a sparse schedule on April 9, the Zurich Zebras rely on two high-leverage leadoff hitters to anchor the daily total. **Colt Keith** (65.26) stands as our top play; hitting at the top of the order against the middling arm of Abel (4.28 xERA) provides a strong floor, with his 10% order bonus and favorable platoon split pushing him into our \"Strong\" tier. **Chase Meidroth** (58.32) remains a marginal start, but he retains his spot due to the scarcity of plate appearances today. While he faces a slight dynamic platoon drag, the projected wind blowing out adds 5% to his efficiency, making him a necessary cog to maintain our offensive output while **Trea Turner**, **Yordan Alvarez**, and **Junior Caminero** sit idle due to team off-days.\n\nThe bench decision process today was effectively dictated by scheduling, as our elite speed threats\u2014specifically **Victor Scott II** and **Caleb Durbin**\u2014are unavailable alongside our core power hitters like **Kyle Schwarber**, **Christian Yelich**, and **Logan O'Hoppe**. Among those technically eligible to play, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** was the most difficult exclusion; he remains high on our internal watch list for his SB ceiling, but with no game today, he provides zero value. We are keeping a close watch on **Kazuma Okamoto**, **Carson Benge**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Josh Smith**, and **Luis Pena** for upcoming series, as the lack of volume today forces us to prioritize the stability of **Colt Keith** and **Chase Meidroth** to avoid unnecessary hits to our season-long game cap management.",
